text.tspan: Share among unvaccinated people who would get a COVID-19 vaccine this
week if it was available to them
Share of survey respondents who have not received a COVID-19 vaccine and who agree with the statement: "If a COVID-19
vaccine were made available to me this week, I would definitely get it."
Source: Imperial College London YouGov Covid 19 Behaviour Tracker Data Hub – Last updated 1 July 2021, 13:30 (London time)
Note: Months containing fewer than 500 survey respondents are excluded. Respondents were presented with a 1 to 5 scale, ranging from
"Strongly agree" (1) to "Strongly disagree" (5). We consider responses of 1 or 2 to be in agreement with the statement.
